    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>OSI Model Demonstration</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 20px;\n            background-color: #f5f5f5;\n        }\n        .container {\n            max-width: 800px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            background: white;\n            padding: 20px;\n            border-radius: 8px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n        }\n        h1 {\n            color: #333;\n            text-align: center;\n        }\n        .osi-model {\n            display: flex;\n            flex-direction: column;\n            margin: 20px 0;\n        }\n        .layer {\n            padding: 15px;\n            margin: 5px 0;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            color: white;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            position: relative;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            transition: all 0.3s;\n        }\n        .layer:hover {\n            transform: scale(1.02);\n        }\n        .layer-info {\n            display: none;\n            padding: 10px;\n            background: #f9f9f9;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            margin-top: 5px;\n            color: #333;\n            font-weight: normal;\n        }\n        .layer-7 { background: #FF5733; } /* Application */\n        .layer-6 { background: #FF8C33; } /* Presentation */\n        .layer-5 { background: #FFC733; } /* Session */\n        .layer-4 { background: #33FF57; } /* Transport */\n        .layer-3 { background: #33A1FF; } /* Network */\n        .layer-2 { background: #8C33FF; } /* Data Link */\n        .layer-1 { background: #FF33A1; } /* Physical */\n        .example {\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            padding: 15px;\n            background: #e9f7ef;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n        }\n        button {\n            background: #4CAF50;\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            padding: 10px 15px;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            margin-top: 10px;\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background: #45a049;\n        }\n        #data-flow {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            min-height: 100px;\n            background: white;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h1>OSI Model Demonstration</h1>\n        \n        <p>The OSI (Open Systems Interconnection) model is a conceptual framework used to understand network interactions in 7 layers.</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"osi-model\">\n            <div class=\"layer layer-7\" onclick=\"toggleInfo(7)\">\n                7. Application Layer\n                <div class=\"layer-info\" id=\"info-7\">\n                    <p>Provides network services directly to user applications. Protocols: HTTP, FTP, SMTP.</p>\n                    <p>Example: Your web browser communicating with a web server.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            <div class=\"layer layer-6\" onclick=\"toggleInfo(6)\">\n                6. Presentation Layer\n                <div class=\"layer-info\" id=\"info-6\">\n                    <p>Translates data between the application and network formats. Handles encryption, compression.</p>\n                    <p>Example: Converting data to JSON/XML, SSL/TLS encryption.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            <div class=\"layer layer-5\" onclick=\"toggleInfo(5)\">\n                5. Session Layer\n                <div class=\"layer-info\" id=\"info-5\">\n                    <p>Manages connections between applications. Establishes, manages, and terminates sessions.</p>\n                    <p>Example: RPC (Remote Procedure Call), NetBIOS.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            <div class=\"layer layer-4\" onclick=\"toggleInfo(4)\">\n                4. Transport Layer\n                <div class=\"layer-info\" id=\"info-4\">\n                    <p>Provides reliable data transfer. Handles flow control, error checking, and data segmentation.</p>\n                    <p>Protocols: TCP (reliable), UDP (unreliable).</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            <div class=\"layer layer-3\" onclick=\"toggleInfo(3)\">\n                3. Network Layer\n                <div class=\"layer-info\" id=\"info-3\">\n                    <p>Handles logical addressing and routing. Determines the best path for data to travel.</p>\n                    <p>Protocols: IP, ICMP. Devices: Routers.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            <div class=\"layer layer-2\" onclick=\"toggleInfo(2)\">\n                2. Data Link Layer\n                <div class=\"layer-info\" id=\"info-2\">\n                    <p>Provides node-to-node data transfer. Handles physical addressing (MAC) and error detection.</p>\n                    <p>Protocols: Ethernet, PPP. Devices: Switches, Bridges.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            <div class=\"layer layer-1\" onclick=\"toggleInfo(1)\">\n                1. Physical Layer\n                <div class=\"layer-info\" id=\"info-1\">\n                    <p>Transmits raw bit stream over physical medium. Defines electrical, mechanical specifications.</p>\n                    <p>Example: Cables, hubs, network interface cards.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div class=\"example\">\n            <h3>Data Flow Example</h3>\n            <p>See how data moves through the OSI layers when sending a web request:</p>\n            <button onclick=\"showDataFlow()\">Show Data Flow</button>\n            <div id=\"data-flow\"></div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        function toggleInfo(layerNum) {\n            const info = document.getElementById(`info-${layerNum}`);\n            if (info.style.display === 'block') {\n                info.style.display = 'none';\n            } else {\n                info.style.display = 'block';\n            }\n        }\n        \n        function showDataFlow() {\n            const dataFlow = document.getElementById('data-flow');\n            dataFlow.innerHTML = '<p>Data flow when requesting a webpage:</p><ol>';\n            \n            // Simulate encapsulation process (top-down)\n            const steps = [\n                \"7: Application - HTTP request created (GET /index.html)\",\n                \"6: Presentation - Data formatted (HTML) and encrypted (HTTPS)\",\n                \"5: Session - Session established with server\",\n                \"4: Transport - TCP segments created with port numbers\",\n                \"3: Network - IP packets created with source/destination IPs\",\n                \"2: Data Link - Frames created with MAC addresses\",\n                \"1: Physical - Bits transmitted over cable/wireless\"\n            ];\n            \n            steps.forEach(step => {\n                dataFlow.innerHTML += `<li>${step}</li>`;\n                // Simulate slight delay between steps\n                setTimeout(() => {}, 100);\n            });\n            \n            dataFlow.innerHTML += '</ol><p>At destination, the process reverses (decapsulation) from Layer 1 up to Layer 7.</p>';\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
